        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(android): queue node events until gateway connect",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCloses #79552.\n\n## Problem\n\nAndroid notification forwarding could send `node.event` before the gateway websocket `connect` request completed. The gateway rejects any first frame that is not `connect`, and Android did not retry the failed notification event, so notification-triggered automations could miss events during reconnect.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`GatewaySession` exposed `currentConnection` before the connect handshake finished. `NodeRuntime` treated a non-null connection as ready and sent notification events directly, while the notification listener had no bounded retry or reconnect reconciliation path.\n\n## Solution\n\n- Publish `currentConnection` only after the gateway connect RPC succeeds.\n- Keep reconnect/disconnect cleanup aware of both connecting and connected sockets.\n- Queue notification events in a bounded FIFO while delivery is unavailable.\n- Flush queued events after reconnect and reconcile active Android notifications that were posted but not delivered.\n- Track delivered posted notifications to avoid duplicate reconnect replays.\n\n## Testing Performed\n\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- Attempted Android focused test:\n  - `./gradlew :app:testPlayDebugUnitTest --tests ai.openclaw.app.gateway.GatewaySessionInvokeTest`\n  - Blocked locally because `JAVA_HOME` is not set and no `java` command is available.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Android `node.event` notification events no longer use a connection until the gateway connect handshake succeeds, and reconnect windows keep notification events queued for later delivery.\n\nReal environment tested: Source-level Android unit-test path in this checkout; local Android runtime tests could not execute because Java is unavailable in the environment.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `git diff --check`; `./gradlew :app:testPlayDebugUnitTest --tests ai.openclaw.app.gateway.GatewaySessionInvokeTest`.\n\nEvidence after fix: `git diff --check` passed. Gradle reported `JAVA_HOME is not set and no 'java' command could be found in your PATH`, so Android test execution was blocked before running tests.\n\nObserved result after fix: Source changes gate `currentConnection` publication behind successful connect and add bounded notification queue/reconnect reconciliation coverage in Android tests.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Android device reconnect, live gateway notification forwarding, and Android Gradle unit execution in this environment due missing Java.\n",
